comment_data.body:
The inspector uses JxBrowser (commercial product) to display DevTools embedded in IntelliJ. To do so, it has to download a couple files. That installation failed for some reason. DevTools works with IJ 2021.2, so I suggest trying to re-install JxBrowser.

To do that, delete the JxBrowser files and restart IntelliJ. The location of the files will vary depending on how you installed IntelliJ. It looks like you are using MacOS, so if you downloaded the IDE and installed it manually then your JxBrowser files will be here" ~/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/IdeaIC2021.2/plugins/flutter-intellij/jxbrowser. Just delete the jxbrowser directory. If you installed it using the JetBrains toolbox, then the path will be different. Look for toolbox and, underneath, something with 2021.2 in its name, then search below that for flutter-intellij/jxbrowser.

If it seems easier, you could re-install IntelliJ instead. If you are using JetBrains toolbox, it should clean up everything. Otherwise, you may have to track down installation artifacts, as described above.

Let us know how it goes.

Without additional information we're unfortunately not sure how to resolve this issue. We're going to close this bug for now, but please don't hesitate to comment on the bug if you have any more information for us; we're happy to reopen. Thanks for your contribution!
